54r.title: Proof that there are infinitely many primes
54r.clickbait: Suppose there were finitely many primes. Then consider the product of all the primes plus 1...
54r.text:
The proof that there are infinitely many [4mf prime numbers] is a [-46z].

Suppose that there were finitely many prime numbers $p_1, p_2, \ldots, p_n$.

Then consider the number $P = p_1p_2\ldots p_n + 1$ — that is, the product of all primes plus 1. It can't be divided by any of the primes in our list because it's 1 more than a multiple of them, so it must either be a prime number itself, or its prime factors are not in our list of primes, contradicting the fact that our list contains all the prime numbers.
